<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-77-0979 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper reports the information obtained as a result of an energy auditperformed on the Italian agricultural industry. Agricultural productsexamined were rice, wheat, corn, potatoes, sugar beets, olives and fruit.Each agricultural product's direct and indirect energy inputs were identified.Taken into account was energy consumed in the use of fertilizers, pesticides,farm equipment (fabrication, depreciation, maintenance), fuels, lubricants,and electricity. The authors caution that socio-economic factors mustbe considered by the analyst when drawing conclusions from this audit.</TEXT></DOC>